A device resembling what appears to be a bomb has been found in a KwaZulu-Natal mosque, which was attacked last week Reaction Unit South Africa (Rusa) spokesperson Prem Balram said his officers evacuated several residences in the Ottawa area and cleared the mosque “after a device resembling a bomb has been found inside the building”. “The device connected to a Nokia mobile phone was found under the Moulana’s [Imam] chair. It was moved by a worshipper.” KZN police spokesperson Captain Nqobile Gwala confirmed that bomb disposal units were on scene to verify the nature of the device. Balram advised the public to stay clear of the area while the police bomb disposal units converged. READ MORE: Attack on mosque described as ‘heinous’ and ‘senseless’ In an earlier incident at the mosque, one person was killed after attackers slit his throat. Two other people were stabbed, and the Imam Hussain Mosque on Old Main Road in Ottawa was set alight on Thursday. – News24